Replaces the regex-only news scanner (which surfaced 0 matches because the
upstream /news returns ~47 BOTTLENECK-classified articles, not a corporate-
actions firehose) with a proper institutional surface.  This tab is now its
own scorecard, NOT a news filter.

5 sub-tabs (URL-routable):

  ALL SITUATIONS — curated event cards with full institutional content
  WHEN TO BUY/SELL — universal timing rules per event archetype
  POST-EVENT PLAYBOOK — J-curve + hold/sell signals + post-tender guidance
  ACCEPTANCE / DEAL MATH — interactive calculators
  DISCOVER — kept the news regex scanner as fallback for new candidates

CURATED EVENTS (v1 ships with 5 active situations):

Tier 1 — Hard Catalyst Trades
  1. Vedanta Ltd — 4-Way Demerger · Record Date May 1, 2026
     Score 21/30 · EV +34.1% · Horizon 18-24mo · BUY
     Full SoP per entity (₹/share ranges with debt/EBITDA notes)
     Post-demerger playbook: HOLD Residual+Cairn / HOLD SMALL Iron+Steel /
     SELL ON POP Aluminium (₹34,510 Cr debt) / SELL QUICKLY Power
  2. Wipro Ltd — ₹15,000 Cr Buyback @ ₹250
     Score 19/30 · BUY_SMALL_ONLY (≤₹2L)
     V2 correction banner: promoters ARE participating (72.63%)
     Acceptance ratio sensitivity table — 4 promoter-tender scenarios
     Small-holder ~40-50% acc / Large-holder 5-7%
  3. Honeywell Aerospace (HONA) — Spin-off · June 29, 2026
     Score 19/30 · EV +33% · BUY HON pre-Investor Day (June 3)
     Distribution ratio still PENDING — flagged as key unknown

Tier 2 — Valuation + Story
  4. QXO / TopBuild (BLD) — Merger Arb (45% cash + 55% stock)
     Score 15/30 · WAIT — currently NEGATIVE spread
     V2 correction: floating-deal effective consideration 74 vs BLD 89
     Live floating-deal calculator with break-even acquirer price
  5. Adobe — $25B Buyback Authorization
     Score 17/30 · CONDITIONAL · Red-flag banner for CFO same-day selling
     Multi-year thesis with explicit conditions to enter

EVERY EVENT CARD INCLUDES:
  - Probability-weighted EV (Bear/Base/Bull) with weighted contribution
  - Fact verification table (CONFIRMED / REVISED / PENDING / RISK_FLAG)
  - Mechanics grid
  - Conditional sections: SoP / Acceptance Math / Floating Deal
  - When-to-buy timing notes
  - Post-event playbook (entity-by-entity actions for demergers)
  - Pros / Cons checklist
  - Warning banner for V2 corrections / red-flag banner for risk events

UNIVERSAL TIMING RULES (4 archetypes):
  Demergers/Spin-offs · Tender Buybacks · Open-Market Buybacks · Merger Arb

POST-EVENT PLAYBOOK:
  J-curve cells (Day 1 to Month 36+) with empirical return ranges
  HOLD signals · SELL signals · post-tender unaccepted-share guidance
  Sourced from Purdue 36-year spin-off study + 2007-2017 replication

INTERACTIVE CALCULATORS (Math tab):
  - Indian Tender Buyback: edit promoter%/public%/buyback price/CMP/etc.
    Live recompute of small-holder vs large-holder acceptance + EV.
    Handles SEBI 15% reserved-category mechanics.
  - Floating Deal: edit cash%/stock-shares-per-target/acquirer-CMP/target-CMP.
    Live recompute of effective consideration + spread + break-even price.

Curated event data is structured as a single CURATED_EVENTS array — adding
or editing an event is a one-record change.  Owner can extend.

V2 CORRECTIONS BANNER at the top of the page lists the 5 corrections from
the master scorecard so the institutional rigour is visible.

